    • Constructor Detail

      • RangePerturbation

        public RangePerturbation(NodeInfo target,
                         int min,
                         int max)
        Create a range restriction. Note that the values should verify 0 >= min <= max < nbval. if min = max, then the component will have a fixed value. Otherwise, a new function will be computed to ensure that the reached leaf belongs to the [min,max] range.
        Parameters:
        target - the restricted component
        min - the minimal value after perturbation
        max - the max value after perturbation

      • update

        public void update(LogicalModel model)
        Description copied from interface: LogicalModelPerturbation
        Apply the perturbation to a model directly (do not create a modified model). This can be used directly when we do not need to preserve the original model. It is also convenient for multiple perturbations, to avoid creating intermediate models.
        Parameters:
        model - the modified model
